        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down. | Bromley. | Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Oct 8.</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>The game cock is the same as what you call the fighting cock. The “duck-wing” is a sub-breed of the game with wings marked as you suppose. “Piles” is another sub-breed of the game with much white about it, &amp; which I do not think worth describing to you. I would suggest in these cases to use within inverted commas the English names.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> “Pencilled” fowls have feathers marked with narrow transverse, dark lines: “Spangled” fowls have feathers tipped with a spot of dark colour; these feathers are said to be “laced” when the dark colour runs some way up both margins.<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>I do not know any proper term for “hackles”; you will see nearly the same elongated feathers on the neck &amp; loins of the cock; those on the loins are often called by Breeders “saddle-feathers”.<ref target="#foot.f4"/> There are two breeds of fowls with black bones; I know of no European name for the breed in which the hens alone are thus characterized.<ref target="#foot.f5"/> You will I hope have received by this time some additional clean sheets.<ref target="#foot.f6"/></p>
<p>Pray keep Newmeister as long as you like.<ref target="#foot.f7"/></p>
<p>I beg you always to ask me any questions you like &amp; believe me my dear Sir | yours very faithfully | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.4 cases] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n2">1.4 within] <hi rend="italic">above del</hi> ‘in’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n3">1.6 spot of] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n4">2.3 by Breeders] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
            
            
            
